    "isnad_matn": {
      "isnad_ar": "",
      "matn_ar": "ثُمَّ قَالَ عَلِيٌّ (عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ): كَانَ فِرَاشُ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ (صَلَّى اللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَآلِهِ) عَبَاءَةً، وَكَانَتْ مِرْفَقَتُهُ أَدَمً، حَشْوُهَا لِيفٌ، فَثُنِيَتْ لَهُ ذَاتَ لَيْلَةٍ، فَلَمَّا أَصْبَحَ قَالَ: لَقَدْ مَنَعَنِي الْفِرَاشُ اللَّيْلَةَ الصَّلَاةَ، فَأَمَرَ (صَلَّى اللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَآلِهِ) أَنْ يُجْعَلَ بِطَاقٍ وَاحِدٍ.",
      "has_chain": false,
      "narrators": []
    },
    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "Imam Ali (AS) recounts the Prophet Muhammad's austere lifestyle. His bed was merely a cloak and a leather cushion stuffed with palm fibre. When Ali folded the bed to make it thicker one night, the Prophet complained in the morning that the added comfort had kept him from his night prayer (tahajjud). He ordered that the bed be restored to just a single layer, demonstrating his preference for simplicity and devotion over physical comfort.",
        "key_terms": {
          "فِرَاش": "Firash -- bed or bedding, here referring to the Prophet's extremely simple sleeping arrangement",
          "الصَّلَاة": "Al-Salah -- prayer, specifically the voluntary night prayer (tahajjud/qiyam al-layl)",
          "بِطَاق": "Bitaq -- a single layer/fold, indicating the Prophet wanted the thinnest possible bed"
        },
        "seo_question": "What was the Prophet Muhammad's bed like and why did he prefer simplicity?"
      },
      "ur": {
